Former South African Airways board chairperson Dudu Myeni has failed to appear before the Commission of Inquiry into State Capture. Myeni appeared before the Commission virtually,in 2020, when she revealed the name of a witness. This after Commission Chairperson, Deputy Chief Justice Raymond Zondo had ordered that the name must be withheld. Myeni’s legal team then requested to make a formal response to the Commission regarding her charge. Myeni also refused to answer any questions claiming that the National Prosecuting Authority would use them against her. Video: Duduzile Myeni’s legal representative asks for a postponement 